galiths and museum mannequins to television shows and best-selling nonfiction – Pitcher demonstrates how prehistory is alive in the twenty-first century, and argues that popular flights back in time provide revealing insights into present-day anxieties, obsessions, and concerns.Back to the Stone Age shows that the human past is not set in stone. By opening up the prehistoric to critical contestation, Pitcher places racial justice at the centre of questions about the existence and persistence of Homo sapiens in the contemporary world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntiquities, Prehistoric. 0aHuman beingsxOrigin. 0aPopular culture. 0aRace. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAnthropocene.  aBelonging.  aBrexit.  aCheddar Man.  aDNA.  aDifference.  aHomo sapiens.  aNeanderthals.  aNeolithic.  aPiltdown.  aRacism.  aStonehenge.  aaffect.  aancestry.  acapitalism.  acaveman.  acitizenship.  acivilization.  aclimate crisis.  acolonialism.  adeep time.  aenvironment.  aevolution.  aextinction.  afeminism.  agender.  agenetics.  ahunter-gatherer.  aimperialism.  aindigenous.  alandscape.  alifestyle.  amannequins.  amegaliths.  anationalism.  anature.  apaleo.  apaleolithic.  apopular culture.  apostcolonial.  aprehistoric.  aprimitivism.  arepresentation.  aspecies.  asurvival.  atime travel.  atribes.  awhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801561140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228015611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228015611/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eB